headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown and Jayson Tatum packed a punch Wednesday night. Dennis Schroder added his own touch.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics take control early, pull away from Pacers 119-100

headlines.description: — The Hornets didn't pop champagne or go wild in the locker room following a win over the Sixers more than five years in the making.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets end 16-game losing streak to 76ers in 109-98 win

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma had 19 points, 10 rebounds and nine assists and the Washington Wizards scored the game's first nine points in a 112-106 victory over the Orlando Magic on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards hand NBA-worst Magic 10th straight loss, 112-106

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro and other young Miami players are finding ways to keep the Heat winning without some of their biggest names.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro's 21 points lead Heat past slumping Hawks, 115-91

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett scored 32 points, Mitchell Robinson had a season-high 19 and the New York Knicks snapped the Dallas Mavericks' six-game winning streak with a 108-85 victory Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks end Mavericks' 6-game win streak with 108-85 victory

events.name: Houston Rockets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Eric Gordon had 31 points and the Houston Rockets overcame Dejounte Murray’s career-high 32 to beat the San Antonio Spurs 128-124 on Wednesday night, snapping a three-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gordon fuels Rockets' rally past Murray, Spurs, 128-124

headlines.description: — Lamar Stevens scored 15 of a career-high 23 points in the third quarter and the Cleveland Cavaliers beat the short-handed Utah Jazz 111-91 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavs rout short-handed Jazz to improve to 3-1 on 6-game trip

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant knew the rest of the league had to be watching, curious to see just how good the Brooklyn Nets can be when they have all their superstars playing.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant, Harden lead Nets to 138-112 romp over Bulls

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox scored 29 points, Chimezie Metu made a clutch 3-pointer with 46.7 seconds remaining and the Sacramento Kings ended their longest losing streak of the season by beating the Los Angeles Lakers 125-116 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James scores 34 but Lakers stumble, fall to Kings 125-116
